  "text": "While daclizumab beta has been removed from the market, understanding of the effects of daclizumab beta may provide insight into the role of NK cells in the pathogenesis of RMS and in the potential of other NK cell-based therapeutic strategies for RMS. Here, we used mass cytometry to profile the NK cells expanded in the setting of daclizumab beta treatment of RMS. As observed previously [CITATION_1] ), daclizumab beta led to a dramatic shift in the NK cell repertoire with an increase in the frequency of CD56 bright NK cells and enhanced expression of NKG2A and CD2. Here, we extended the characterization of the phenotype, demonstrating that the expanded CD56 bright NK cells had a unique phenotype that was present by 24 weeks of treatment.",
